1
00:00:01,411 --> 00:00:02,679
Romantic Doctor, Teacher Kim

2
00:00:21,054 --> 00:00:22,756
DEATH CERTIFICATE

3
00:00:28,662 --> 00:00:30,497
CAUSE OF DEATH: DEATH FROM DISEASE

4
00:00:31,932 --> 00:00:33,233
NAME: KANG DONG-JOO

5
00:00:34,501 --> 00:00:37,504
What... is this?

6
00:00:37,571 --> 00:00:41,508
All you have to do is
sign that and save it as it is.

7
00:00:43,177 --> 00:00:45,312
This patient hasn't died yet.

8
00:00:45,379 --> 00:00:47,014
He's still alive.

9
00:00:48,081 --> 00:00:48,949
Then, why should I...

10
00:00:49,016 --> 00:00:50,617
His BP keeps dropping.

11
00:00:50,684 --> 00:00:52,119
He's not passing any urine, either.

12
00:00:52,186 --> 00:00:54,388
If he's showing no stem signs
after going into cardiac arrest,

13
00:00:54,454 --> 00:00:55,989
he's pretty much brain-dead.

14
00:00:56,056 --> 00:00:57,090
Some patients who have...

15
00:00:57,157 --> 00:00:59,259
...a return of spontaneous circulation
don't show stem signs.

16
00:00:59,326 --> 00:01:01,261
We can't make those kinds of judgments...

17
00:01:01,328 --> 00:01:03,488
...until we've monitored him
for at least a day or two.

18
00:01:04,798 --> 00:01:06,877
And on top of that,
"Cause of Death: Death from disease?"

19
00:01:06,967 --> 00:01:09,703
Here are military hospital records
regarding Private Park.

20
00:01:10,304 --> 00:01:12,039
It seemed that...

21
00:01:12,105 --> 00:01:14,625
...he'd been receiving treatment
for diverticulitis for a while.

22
00:01:14,741 --> 00:01:15,709
Here, for your reference.

23
00:01:15,776 --> 00:01:16,677
It wasn't diverticulitis!

24
00:01:16,743 --> 00:01:19,079
He had a bowel perforation
due to blunt force trauma!

25
00:01:19,146 --> 00:01:21,114
I opened him up and saw that for myself!

26
00:01:21,181 --> 00:01:22,382
He's a deserter!

27
00:01:23,283 --> 00:01:26,486
And on top of that,
he was treated due to physical injuries.

28
00:01:26,553 --> 00:01:29,990
Think about how sensitive
this issue could become.

29
00:01:30,924 --> 00:01:34,494
Imagine what would happen
if the press found out about this.

30
00:01:34,561 --> 00:01:39,132
The internet and such will be
buzzing about this news.

31
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,102
And all of this will end with
some midlevel manager...

32
00:01:42,169 --> 00:01:44,538
...who did nothing wrong
being forced to quit.

33
00:01:45,205 --> 00:01:47,374
We can't be so irresponsible
as to let that happen.

34
00:01:50,644 --> 00:01:51,778
So...

35
00:01:54,047 --> 00:01:58,485
...are you telling me to lie?

36
00:02:02,923 --> 00:02:04,725
I'm telling you to
make the rational choice.

37
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:06,293
Exactly!

38
00:02:08,996 --> 00:02:11,796
So you're telling me to write
a death certificate that is full of lies.

39
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:15,769
And for a living person, at that...

40
00:02:17,104 --> 00:02:18,639
...and sign it?

41
00:02:20,774 --> 00:02:22,476
Sometimes, in life...

42
00:02:23,210 --> 00:02:25,913
...being silent is
more important than the truth.

43
00:02:26,847 --> 00:02:28,715
Just think of this as
one of those moments.

44
00:02:34,087 --> 00:02:38,825
I'm sorry, but I'll pretend that
this meeting never happened.

45
00:02:40,630 --> 00:02:42,065
Kang Dong-joo!

46
00:02:55,209 --> 00:02:57,477
Letting yourself get held back
by your own sense of justice...

47
00:02:57,544 --> 00:02:59,580
...is what you do when you're immature.

48
00:03:01,882 --> 00:03:03,217
But you're an adult now.

49
00:03:04,084 --> 00:03:07,321
As a doctor, and as a
contributing member of society,

50
00:03:08,088 --> 00:03:10,490
you need to take on more responsibility.

51
00:03:11,158 --> 00:03:12,125
Okay?

52
00:03:13,327 --> 00:03:18,165
Let's settle this quietly and simply,
Kang Dong-joo.

53
00:03:33,213 --> 00:03:34,381
What is the meaning of this?

54
00:03:35,649 --> 00:03:37,184
What are you doing here?

55
00:03:45,425 --> 00:03:47,494
All of you are gathered here like this.

56
00:03:48,562 --> 00:03:51,265
Just what are you plotting
this time around?

57
00:03:51,331 --> 00:03:52,332
Huh?

58
00:04:01,808 --> 00:04:02,809
Director?

59
00:04:29,703 --> 00:04:30,604
EPISODE 12

60
00:04:30,671 --> 00:04:32,039
Yong-gyun.

61
00:04:33,707 --> 00:04:35,108
What about our Joo-hyuk?

62
00:04:35,175 --> 00:04:36,143
Huh?

63
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:37,611
How's Joo-hyuk?

64
00:04:58,479 --> 00:05:00,247
Oh, my child!

65
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:04,304
Joo-hyuk!

66
00:05:05,105 --> 00:05:06,673
Joo-hyuk!

67
00:05:12,312 --> 00:05:14,081
Joo-hyuk!

68
00:05:20,687 --> 00:05:21,855
Joo-hyuk.

69
00:05:22,956 --> 00:05:25,726
Oh... oh my!

70
00:05:28,195 --> 00:05:29,129
Oh my.

71
00:05:32,566 --> 00:05:34,126
He's going into cardiac arrest, Doctor!

72
00:05:35,035 --> 00:05:36,803
Nurse Oh! Call Dr Kang Dong-joo!

73
00:05:38,539 --> 00:05:40,699
We ask that the guardians leave
for just a bit, please.

74
00:05:40,917 --> 00:05:41,951
Just a moment, ma'am.

75
00:05:42,042 --> 00:05:43,143
-Just a moment.
-Ma'am?

76
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:44,178
Just a moment.

77
00:05:52,152 --> 00:05:53,420
Oh... oh no.

78
00:05:54,288 --> 00:05:56,123
Oh... Doctor!

79
00:05:56,390 --> 00:05:57,858
ER

80
00:06:01,875 --> 00:06:03,410
Yes, Nurse Oh. I'm on my way now.

81
00:06:11,642 --> 00:06:13,802
-What happened?
-He's gone into cardiac arrest again!

82
00:06:14,474 --> 00:06:15,754
Hurry and get the defibrillator.

83
00:06:25,085 --> 00:06:27,588
DEATH CERTIFICATE NAME: PARK JOO-HYUK

84
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:31,491
200 joules.

85
00:06:34,879 --> 00:06:35,946
Back away.

86
00:06:37,038 --> 00:06:38,273
Clear!

87
00:06:39,733 --> 00:06:40,868
I'll do more compressions.

88
00:06:41,088 --> 00:06:42,122
Here, I'll do them.

89
00:06:50,717 --> 00:06:51,837
Checking his heart rate now.

90
00:06:55,816 --> 00:06:56,850
One more time.

91
00:06:56,917 --> 00:06:57,985
200 joules!

92
00:06:58,785 --> 00:06:59,786
Ready, Doctor.

93
00:07:01,955 --> 00:07:03,156
Clear!

94
00:07:12,443 --> 00:07:13,778
You have to live.

95
00:07:14,574 --> 00:07:15,976
You're still so young!

96
00:07:16,301 --> 00:07:17,970
You have to live!

97
00:07:25,012 --> 00:07:26,880
CAUSE OF DEATH: DEATH FROM DISEASE

98
00:07:30,984 --> 00:07:33,109
You have to live.

99
00:07:33,263 --> 00:07:34,264
Darn it.

100
00:07:38,358 --> 00:07:39,626
Dr Kang...

101
00:08:02,577 --> 00:08:04,079
Time of death...

102
00:08:05,786 --> 00:08:07,855
20:48.

103
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,442
NAME: KANG DONG-JOO

104
00:08:41,822 --> 00:08:45,959
EPISODE 12
Boiling Point

105
00:08:49,561 --> 00:08:51,163
-This one?
-The one in the back.

106
00:08:51,254 --> 00:08:52,255
Yes, ma'am.

107
00:08:58,797 --> 00:08:59,865
Excuse me.

108
00:09:00,407 --> 00:09:03,177
How do I get to Doldam Hospital?

109
00:09:15,222 --> 00:09:19,026
What happened was quite unfortunate.

110
00:09:19,793 --> 00:09:24,331
The military will cooperate with you
fully regarding the funeral procession.

111
00:09:24,798 --> 00:09:26,099
Thank you.

112
00:09:27,501 --> 00:09:29,436
I'm sorry enough that
he became a deserter.

113
00:09:30,804 --> 00:09:32,806
And yet, you're going above
and beyond for us.

114
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:35,342
If you ever need assistance,

115
00:09:35,409 --> 00:09:37,110
please contact me anytime.

116
00:09:38,445 --> 00:09:39,613
Goodbye, then.

117
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:45,285
Joo-hyuk was murdered!

118
00:09:52,226 --> 00:09:58,265
What... do you mean by that, Yong-gyun?

119
00:09:58,398 --> 00:10:01,568
Three of his superiors would
subject him to physical punishments...

120
00:10:01,635 --> 00:10:02,870
...and hit him all the time for no reason.

121
00:10:02,936 --> 00:10:04,938
That's why he didn't return to the base.

122
00:10:05,005 --> 00:10:06,807
That's why he died!

123
00:10:06,874 --> 00:10:08,075
Look here, young man!

124
00:10:16,049 --> 00:10:19,987
You can't say things like that
when nothing has been confirmed.

125
00:10:21,672 --> 00:10:24,508
I'm sure that you'd upset
Mr Park's parents...

126
00:10:24,758 --> 00:10:26,293
...even more by doing so.

127
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:28,862
The doctor in charge of
his surgery said that, too.

128
00:10:29,696 --> 00:10:32,165
He said that it was due to getting hit
that Joo-hyuk ended up like that!

129
00:10:32,232 --> 00:10:35,002
And I heard him talking to you, myself!

130
00:10:39,339 --> 00:10:41,308
I definitely heard him say that, Mister.

131
00:10:42,276 --> 00:10:44,411
If you go and ask
the doctor in charge of him...

132
00:10:45,112 --> 00:10:46,672
...I'm sure he'll answer us truthfully.

133
00:10:48,445 --> 00:10:50,647
And where can I...

134
00:10:50,817 --> 00:10:52,619
...go to meet this doctor?

135
00:10:54,655 --> 00:10:56,323
I'll escort you there.

136
00:10:59,092 --> 00:11:00,494
Please follow me.

137
00:11:00,561 --> 00:11:02,129
DEATH CERTIFICATE

138
00:11:02,196 --> 00:11:04,431
Just do it this once.

139
00:11:05,465 --> 00:11:07,100
I'll be real for a second.

140
00:11:07,167 --> 00:11:09,703
You think I'm living like this
because I love Director Do?

141
00:11:10,771 --> 00:11:12,573
It's so I don't fall
out of his good graces.

142
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:14,875
It's so I can stick by him and
live a nice life...

143
00:11:14,942 --> 00:11:17,678
...instead of a shoddy one.

144
00:11:18,512 --> 00:11:21,515
At your age, that doesn't seem
that important, right?

145
00:11:21,982 --> 00:11:23,622
Just wait until you
get to my age, though.

146
00:11:24,117 --> 00:11:26,086
When you whiz past your 40s and
your 50s are just around the corner...

147
00:11:26,153 --> 00:11:28,322
...the situation itself changes entirely!

148
00:11:28,655 --> 00:11:30,524
Who you side with can...

149
00:11:30,591 --> 00:11:32,793
...change your entire world!

150
00:11:36,563 --> 00:11:40,100
All you have to do is be
obedient to Director Do.

151
00:11:40,834 --> 00:11:42,669
If you just do that,

152
00:11:43,804 --> 00:11:45,472
your entire life will change forever!

153
00:11:46,473 --> 00:11:47,407
Got it?

154
00:11:54,147 --> 00:11:55,549
Dr Kang Dong-joo.

155
00:11:56,617 --> 00:11:58,099
Patient Park Joo-hyuk's
parents would like to...

156
00:11:58,189 --> 00:12:00,625
...ask you a couple of things.

157
00:12:01,455 --> 00:12:02,523
Do you have time?

158
00:12:05,726 --> 00:12:06,894
Please come in.

159
00:12:15,002 --> 00:12:16,003
Hello.

160
00:12:17,371 --> 00:12:19,873
I'm Joo-hyuk's father.

161
00:12:20,874 --> 00:12:22,476
I heard that you said

162
00:12:24,311 --> 00:12:27,080
Joo-hyuk may have been beaten up.

163
00:12:28,715 --> 00:12:29,816
Is this true?

164
00:12:39,726 --> 00:12:41,261
Please, Doctor.

165
00:12:45,799 --> 00:12:50,037
He was healthy two months ago,
when he was on leave.

166
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:53,006
So how did he end up like that?

167
00:12:54,374 --> 00:12:56,543
We need to know the reason why.

168
00:13:00,881 --> 00:13:05,552
Please tell us what you know, Doctor.

169
00:13:07,521 --> 00:13:08,622
Please.

170
00:13:13,227 --> 00:13:14,294
Doctor.

171
00:13:17,564 --> 00:13:19,833
What are you doing, Dr Kang Dong-joo?

172
00:13:20,634 --> 00:13:22,369
Hurry up and say something.

173
00:13:29,276 --> 00:13:30,377
I...

174
00:13:32,179 --> 00:13:34,348
...need to look into
this matter a bit further.

175
00:13:37,651 --> 00:13:40,087
And I have to confirm the records...

176
00:13:40,153 --> 00:13:43,156
...saying that your son was
treated at a military hospital.

177
00:13:44,858 --> 00:13:47,094
It will take some more time for me to...

178
00:13:48,629 --> 00:13:50,430
...finish writing the death certificate.

179
00:13:54,034 --> 00:13:55,269
Excuse me.

180
00:14:34,775 --> 00:14:35,735
Are you going somewhere?

181
00:14:37,544 --> 00:14:38,946
I'm just getting some fresh air.

182
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:40,781
Why did you do that?

183
00:14:41,348 --> 00:14:42,249
What are you talking about?

184
00:14:42,316 --> 00:14:44,718
There were bruises on
Mr Park Joo-hyuk's body.

185
00:14:45,252 --> 00:14:48,322
And you confirmed that he had
a bowel perforation due to trauma.

186
00:14:48,388 --> 00:14:49,389
You should've told them all that.

187
00:14:49,456 --> 00:14:50,696
So why didn't you say anything?

188
00:14:52,593 --> 00:14:53,994
Are you even listening to me?

189
00:14:54,595 --> 00:14:55,696
Hello?

190
00:14:57,564 --> 00:14:59,199
I asked if you were listening to me,

191
00:14:59,266 --> 00:15:00,567
Dr Kang Dong-joo.

192
00:15:01,535 --> 00:15:03,737
I'm just tired, that is all.

193
00:15:03,804 --> 00:15:04,705
Let's talk later.

194
00:15:14,248 --> 00:15:15,482
What's with him?

195
00:15:35,636 --> 00:15:37,304
Welcome!

196
00:15:38,705 --> 00:15:39,773
Kang Dong-joo!

197
00:15:48,448 --> 00:15:50,517
I'm sorry if I interrupted you two.

198
00:15:50,584 --> 00:15:52,286
Oh no, not at all!

199
00:15:52,352 --> 00:15:53,887
Hey, hey! Not at all!

200
00:15:53,954 --> 00:15:55,088
You didn't interrupt anything,
so come in.

201
00:15:55,155 --> 00:15:56,323
Come in!

202
00:15:56,957 --> 00:15:57,797
Well?

203
00:15:58,025 --> 00:16:00,227
Are you here for a drink,
or to have dinner?

204
00:16:00,294 --> 00:16:01,574
Please give me a bottle of soju.

205
00:16:02,129 --> 00:16:03,197
Sure.

206
00:16:17,277 --> 00:16:18,745
MOTHER

207
00:16:23,517 --> 00:16:24,651
Taxi!

208
00:16:40,634 --> 00:16:41,474
Drink up.

209
00:16:42,035 --> 00:16:43,370
I'm buying.

210
00:16:44,271 --> 00:16:45,172
Go ahead and drink.

211
00:16:57,551 --> 00:16:58,952
Drink up.

212
00:17:00,587 --> 00:17:03,924
You don't have to drink
if you don't think you can handle it.

213
00:17:05,125 --> 00:17:08,362
No, I can drink.

214
00:17:14,434 --> 00:17:15,903
Would you like another?

215
00:17:16,637 --> 00:17:18,005
Yes.

216
00:17:27,314 --> 00:17:28,749
A drinking contest?

217
00:17:28,815 --> 00:17:30,217
Between Teacher Kim and Dr Kang?

218
00:17:30,284 --> 00:17:31,518
A drinking contest?

219
00:17:32,319 --> 00:17:33,720
That's what he's telling me.

220
00:17:33,921 --> 00:17:35,289
How much have they had to drink?

221
00:17:35,355 --> 00:17:37,724
They just opened
their eighth bottle of soju.

222
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:39,193
Eight bottles?

223
00:17:50,637 --> 00:17:52,105
Since when have you known?

224
00:17:52,639 --> 00:17:53,507
Huh?

225
00:17:53,874 --> 00:17:55,242
That it was me.

226
00:17:57,711 --> 00:18:01,114
That I was the one who wreaked havoc
in that ER back then.

227
00:18:02,716 --> 00:18:04,685
Since when have you known?

228
00:18:04,751 --> 00:18:06,553
Let me ask you something, too.

229
00:18:07,487 --> 00:18:09,189
Why did you become a doctor?

230
00:18:11,692 --> 00:18:13,594
Well, you said to me...

231
00:18:14,628 --> 00:18:16,864
that if I wanted to get revenge,

232
00:18:16,930 --> 00:18:18,699
I should do it with my skill.

233
00:18:20,167 --> 00:18:21,668
And I did just that.

234
00:18:22,002 --> 00:18:25,439
So I could show people
that I wasn't a pushover.

235
00:18:27,774 --> 00:18:30,277
Because I wanted to make it impossible...

236
00:18:31,144 --> 00:18:33,914
...for those who looked down on me
to look down on me any longer.

237
00:18:36,016 --> 00:18:38,785
Because I wanted to show them that...

238
00:18:40,854 --> 00:18:42,494
...I'm a different human being than them.

239
00:18:42,623 --> 00:18:43,824
But, you know...

240
00:18:45,559 --> 00:18:47,928
...judging from the decisions you make,

241
00:18:48,595 --> 00:18:50,597
you're not much different than them.

242
00:18:50,731 --> 00:18:52,599
Because nothing else works.

243
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:55,502
Because I have to get to the top,
no matter what it takes.

244
00:18:55,936 --> 00:18:57,604
That's the only way...

245
00:18:57,671 --> 00:19:00,107
I'll be able to face off
against Director Do, or whomever.

246
00:19:01,542 --> 00:19:03,343
So...

247
00:19:03,777 --> 00:19:06,380
...if you accept his offer of a 15
percent raise in your annual salary...

248
00:19:06,446 --> 00:19:10,884
...as well as 100,000 dollars for
your research every year you think...

249
00:19:11,318 --> 00:19:13,787
...that'll help you rise in the ranks?

250
00:19:14,254 --> 00:19:16,623
You'll have to become
obedient to Director Do...

251
00:19:16,823 --> 00:19:19,026
...and pledge your loyalty to him.

252
00:19:19,092 --> 00:19:22,729
Yeah?
And then, you'll be promoted to Chief...

253
00:19:23,063 --> 00:19:25,866
...and your name will be in
all of the scientific journals!

254
00:19:27,134 --> 00:19:31,471
Will you finally have achieved
the success you so desired then?

255
00:19:31,538 --> 00:19:33,507
Isn't that how the world works?

256
00:19:35,876 --> 00:19:39,479
That's what this world
qualifies as "success."

257
00:19:40,881 --> 00:19:42,850
Because if I don't take someone's side,

258
00:19:42,916 --> 00:19:45,619
I'll become less than nothing.

259
00:19:45,686 --> 00:19:50,891
So you throw away your self-esteem
and your conscience for that?

260
00:19:51,959 --> 00:19:53,460
And cast your sense of shame...

261
00:19:53,794 --> 00:19:54,962
...into the wind?

262
00:19:55,028 --> 00:19:57,064
Can I protect my pride...

263
00:19:59,132 --> 00:20:00,934
...if I live as less than nothing?

264
00:20:03,036 --> 00:20:05,439
Can I protect my conscience when...

265
00:20:07,074 --> 00:20:09,510
...I'm completely powerless?

266
00:20:17,150 --> 00:20:21,788
Do you know how hellish and painful
