00:37:29,883 --> 00:37:31,885
But the facts aren't always right.

527
00:37:32,986 --> 00:37:35,923
What kind of nonsense is that,
all of the sudden?

528
00:37:38,659 --> 00:37:39,593
He was a deserter.

529
00:37:40,093 --> 00:37:42,533
So imagine if it was revealed that
he died an unnatural death.

530
00:37:42,896 --> 00:37:44,498
There would be uproar.

531
00:37:45,499 --> 00:37:48,468
That could have
so many detrimental effects.

532
00:37:49,803 --> 00:37:51,305
So I can't not think it over.

533
00:37:51,371 --> 00:37:53,874
Like I said, why do you need to
think about this at all?

534
00:37:54,541 --> 00:37:57,344
You're merely a doctor and the doctor
who was in charge of him.

535
00:37:57,744 --> 00:38:00,113
All doctors have to do
is deliver the facts.

536
00:38:05,652 --> 00:38:06,787
Wait...

537
00:38:08,655 --> 00:38:11,015
...is stuff like this included
in the terms you agreed to...

538
00:38:12,359 --> 00:38:14,517
...in exchange for your
15 percent pay raise,

539
00:38:14,608 --> 00:38:16,488
and extra 100,000 dollars
for your research?

540
00:38:21,535 --> 00:38:22,503
See, what did I tell you?

541
00:38:22,569 --> 00:38:24,569
I warned you that something
like this would happen.

542
00:38:24,671 --> 00:38:26,874
I told you that you'd have to
sell your conscience away.

543
00:38:26,940 --> 00:38:28,876
That's not it, so don't make
baseless assumptions.

544
00:38:28,942 --> 00:38:29,843
You're denying it now?

545
00:38:32,880 --> 00:38:34,181
Please, just...

546
00:38:35,382 --> 00:38:37,017
...leave me alone for a bit.

547
00:38:44,391 --> 00:38:46,493
It goes without saying
that you should do this...

548
00:38:47,403 --> 00:38:50,403
...when it comes to other things
but something like a death certificate...

549
00:38:51,999 --> 00:38:54,538
...shouldn't have its facts altered
due to outside influences.

550
00:38:54,629 --> 00:38:55,559
You know that, right?

551
00:38:57,638 --> 00:38:59,540
If you find your resolve shaken...

552
00:39:01,275 --> 00:39:03,343
...even just a little because of that...

553
00:39:06,180 --> 00:39:07,681
I really...

554
00:39:09,516 --> 00:39:11,357
...may end up truly,
truly disappointed in you.

555
00:39:17,624 --> 00:39:18,559
Dr Kang Dong-joo.

556
00:39:18,992 --> 00:39:20,460
The police are outside.

557
00:39:20,961 --> 00:39:22,362
This person killed my father.

558
00:39:22,429 --> 00:39:24,264
Excuse me! Doing this here is illegal!

559
00:39:24,331 --> 00:39:26,667
-Let go!
-And this is a hospital!

560
00:39:26,767 --> 00:39:30,003
If you want to protest, you need to get
permission at the police station first!

561
00:39:30,070 --> 00:39:31,238
This person killed my father!

562
00:39:31,305 --> 00:39:32,639
He's Dr Kang Dong-joo, and he works here!

563
00:39:32,706 --> 00:39:33,774
-Hey!
-Please read it over!

564
00:39:33,841 --> 00:39:34,875
I told you, you can't do this!

565
00:39:34,942 --> 00:39:36,043
This person killed my father!

566
00:39:36,109 --> 00:39:37,611
He's Dr Kang Dong-joo, and he works here!

567
00:39:37,678 --> 00:39:39,580
I'm not leaving! Let go!

568
00:40:08,654 --> 00:40:09,789
I'm sorry.

569
00:40:10,677 --> 00:40:11,979
What are you doing?

570
00:40:12,679 --> 00:40:14,081
Ma'am, why are you...

571
00:40:19,253 --> 00:40:20,733
That Kang Dong-joo, who works here...

572
00:40:24,291 --> 00:40:25,425
...is my son.

573
00:40:32,933 --> 00:40:35,102
My son did something unforgivable.

574
00:40:36,170 --> 00:40:37,838
This is all due to my own shortcomings.

575
00:40:38,539 --> 00:40:40,340
I guess that's why
he did something like that.

576
00:40:41,275 --> 00:40:42,976
I apologize.

577
00:40:43,210 --> 00:40:44,511
Please, forgive him.

578
00:40:44,945 --> 00:40:46,380
I apologize.

579
00:40:51,351 --> 00:40:52,452
I apologize.

580
00:40:54,087 --> 00:40:55,055
Mother...

581
00:40:55,122 --> 00:40:57,401
There's nothing left to say.
You were the one in the wrong.

582
00:40:57,491 --> 00:40:58,492
Apologize to her, now.

583
00:41:04,698 --> 00:41:07,167
Have you forgotten
how your own father passed away?

584
00:41:07,868 --> 00:41:09,703
So how could you do that to someone else?

585
00:41:09,770 --> 00:41:11,805
There's no excuse for what you did!

586
00:41:15,943 --> 00:41:19,513
Apologize to her 100... 1,000 times
until she's satisfied.

587
00:41:21,081 --> 00:41:22,015
Now!

588
00:41:37,431 --> 00:41:38,599
Please...

589
00:41:40,467 --> 00:41:41,635
...leave this person alone.

590
00:41:41,935 --> 00:41:42,936
What?

591
00:41:43,470 --> 00:41:45,739
But we received a report,
so I'm afraid we can't.

592
00:41:46,006 --> 00:41:47,407
It's okay.

593
00:41:49,276 --> 00:41:52,946
Leave her alone to do as she pleases.

594
00:42:12,966 --> 00:42:14,768
I truly have no excuses...

595
00:42:15,836 --> 00:42:17,204
...to offer for what I've done.

596
00:42:18,539 --> 00:42:20,407
I wish I could go back to that moment...

597
00:42:22,075 --> 00:42:26,613
...and make things right.

598
00:42:28,782 --> 00:42:31,018
I'm filled with regret...

599
00:42:33,020 --> 00:42:34,382
...and am embarrassed of myself.

600
00:42:37,758 --> 00:42:38,992
You little brat...

601
00:42:45,265 --> 00:42:46,834
I truly... truly apologize,

602
00:42:48,502 --> 00:42:49,703
from the bottom of my heart.

603
00:42:54,274 --> 00:42:55,742
You little brat...!

604
00:43:00,447 --> 00:43:01,982
Bring my father back to life!

605
00:43:02,449 --> 00:43:03,784
You little brat...!

606
00:43:04,418 --> 00:43:06,286
Bring my father back to life!

607
00:43:09,356 --> 00:43:11,625
Bring my father back to life.

608
00:43:17,698 --> 00:43:18,899
Father!

609
00:43:26,907 --> 00:43:28,442
Father!

610
00:43:35,015 --> 00:43:36,049
Father!

611
00:43:38,685 --> 00:43:39,920
Father!

612
00:43:42,756 --> 00:43:44,291
Father!

613
00:43:49,963 --> 00:43:51,598
Father!

614
00:44:09,016 --> 00:44:10,918
GEOSAN UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

615
00:44:16,823 --> 00:44:18,058
Isn't that Bu Yong-joo?

616
00:44:18,725 --> 00:44:19,960
So that's Bu Yong-joo?

617
00:44:20,594 --> 00:44:22,062
It is him! Dr Bu Yong-joo!

618
00:44:22,462 --> 00:44:23,530
Why is he here?

619
00:44:27,234 --> 00:44:28,702
Director Do. Yes, it's me.

620
00:44:29,937 --> 00:44:30,804
What?

621
00:44:31,205 --> 00:44:32,506
Who came to the hospital, now?

622
00:44:57,030 --> 00:44:58,465
You can't do this, sir!

623
00:44:58,532 --> 00:45:00,033
I told you, you can't!

624
00:45:02,503 --> 00:45:03,937
I'll call you back later.

625
00:45:07,274 --> 00:45:08,308
Oh ho.

626
00:45:09,309 --> 00:45:13,280
What brings you all the way here,
Dr Bu Yong-joo?

627
00:45:13,947 --> 00:45:15,616
I have something to say to you.

628
00:45:16,817 --> 00:45:18,151
I'm sure that a phone call
would've been sufficient.

629
00:45:18,218 --> 00:45:19,458
Why did you come all the way...

630
00:45:22,890 --> 00:45:24,324
What the heck are you doing?

631
00:45:28,595 --> 00:45:29,496
Hey.

632
00:45:29,963 --> 00:45:32,699
Don't ever come back to
Doldam Hospital again.

633
00:45:33,233 --> 00:45:37,237
And stop using young people to
satisfy your own greed.

634
00:45:37,704 --> 00:45:41,074
Stop clinging on to
Kang Dong-joo and Yoon Seo-Jung...

635
00:45:41,141 --> 00:45:43,141
...and trying to mess with them,
you little brat...

636
00:45:45,812 --> 00:45:46,932
Because from this moment on,

637
00:45:48,515 --> 00:45:50,584
I won't just sit and watch.

638
00:45:50,651 --> 00:45:51,518
You got that?

639
00:46:01,595 --> 00:46:02,963
Aren't you ashamed of yourself?

640
00:46:04,998 --> 00:46:09,570
What the heck are you trying to do
by toying with some kids, at your age?

641
00:46:12,306 --> 00:46:13,774
Pathetic little brat...

642
00:46:20,147 --> 00:46:21,849
DEATH CERTIFICATE

643
00:46:35,929 --> 00:46:36,930
This is...

644
00:46:38,465 --> 00:46:40,234
...your son's death certificate.

645
00:46:49,910 --> 00:46:51,378
CAUSE OF DEATH: DEATH FROM DISEASE

646
00:47:11,932 --> 00:47:12,900
And this...

647
00:47:13,500 --> 00:47:17,738
...is a recording of the
surgery on your son that I performed.

648
00:47:19,206 --> 00:47:20,874
It will definitely
be sufficient evidence.

649
00:47:21,542 --> 00:47:23,877
And if you need my testimony to...

650
00:47:24,745 --> 00:47:28,916
...uncover the truth, by any chance...

651
00:47:30,117 --> 00:47:31,705
...please feel free to call me anytime.

652
00:47:40,594 --> 00:47:45,933
My wife wants me to tell you
that she says "Thank you."

653
00:48:01,715 --> 00:48:03,250
I apologize...

654
00:48:05,385 --> 00:48:07,254
...for getting this to you so late, ma'am.

655
00:48:10,691 --> 00:48:12,226
Oh, it's okay.

656
00:48:13,427 --> 00:48:20,427
We're satisfied enough with knowing
the truth behind our son's death.

657
00:48:21,268 --> 00:48:22,669
Thank you!

658
00:48:24,371 --> 00:48:25,539
Thank you!

659
00:48:51,164 --> 00:48:52,165
What the heck is this?

660
00:48:52,933 --> 00:48:54,902
CAUSE OF DEATH: DEATH FROM DISEASE

661
00:48:54,968 --> 00:48:57,905
Kang Dong-joo... is he out of his mind?

662
00:49:00,574 --> 00:49:02,509
Hey, Kang Dong-joo!

663
00:49:03,710 --> 00:49:04,550
Are you insane?

664
00:49:05,012 --> 00:49:05,972
Have you lost your mind?

665
00:49:07,014 --> 00:49:08,715
What the heck are you trying to do, here?

666
00:49:09,283 --> 00:49:10,918
All I did was do as I was taught.

667
00:49:12,653 --> 00:49:17,491
"A patient's death certificate
is the last bit of courtesy..."

668
00:49:18,892 --> 00:49:20,227
"...that a doctor can extend
toward the deceased's family."

669
00:49:20,294 --> 00:49:22,614
Why can't you get what
I'm saying through your thick skull?

670
00:49:23,764 --> 00:49:27,334
Director Do's orders were to
nip this matter in the bud.

671
00:49:28,368 --> 00:49:31,138
Do you not know what it means to
defy Director Do's orders?

672
00:49:31,271 --> 00:49:32,339
I'm fully aware!

673
00:49:33,707 --> 00:49:34,708
And...

674
00:49:36,076 --> 00:49:38,545
...I'm aware of how debasing
it'd be to obey him, too.

675
00:49:38,645 --> 00:49:41,481
Is it that hard to
let just one matter slide?

676
00:49:43,283 --> 00:49:47,020
I just didn't want
to be caught in the act.

677
00:49:48,088 --> 00:49:49,423
What?

678
00:49:50,390 --> 00:49:51,658
And...

679
00:49:52,793 --> 00:49:55,295
...I thought this might be
an okay place to act as if...

680
00:49:55,362 --> 00:49:58,866
...I were actually a decent guy.

681
00:49:59,833 --> 00:50:01,502
That's what I thought.

682
00:50:04,338 --> 00:50:07,708
About Doldam Hospital, I mean.

683
00:50:09,109 --> 00:50:12,980
By that, are you implying that
you don't care if you never...

684
00:50:13,046 --> 00:50:15,549
...go back to the main hospital?

685
00:50:16,884 --> 00:50:19,004
Are you confident that
you'll never regret doing this?

686
00:50:21,855 --> 00:50:22,823
Perhaps.

687
00:50:43,243 --> 00:50:46,313
I'm sorry you had to see that side of me.

688
00:50:47,047 --> 00:50:51,552
Did you think a job that entails
saving lives would be that simple?

689
00:50:52,486 --> 00:50:55,622
A lot of things can happen
when you have a job like that.

690
00:50:59,092 --> 00:51:01,195
I don't think I'll be able
to go back to the...

691
00:51:01,261 --> 00:51:03,230
...main hospital for the time being.

692
00:51:03,564 --> 00:51:08,035
Well, the hospital you're at now
doesn't seem half bad.

693
00:51:09,436 --> 00:51:13,473
And... I quite liked that young lady
you called "Dr Yoon."

694
00:51:14,208 --> 00:51:15,876
Young lady I called "Dr Yoon"?

695
00:51:16,844 --> 00:51:17,945
You know.

696
00:51:18,412 --> 00:51:21,215
The one you call
"Dr Seo-Jung," or something.

697
00:51:21,949 --> 00:51:23,189
The doctor who works in the ER.

698
00:51:24,284 --> 00:51:26,854
How do you know Dr Seo-Jung, Mom?

699
00:51:28,655 --> 00:51:30,891
You really don't remember anything?

700
00:51:31,825 --> 00:51:34,695
Did you really black out completely?

701
00:51:35,028 --> 00:51:36,697
What happened?

702
00:51:38,765 --> 00:51:42,135
If you're curious, go ask her yourself.

703
00:51:42,736 --> 00:51:44,204
You may be my son and all,

704
00:51:44,838 --> 00:51:47,140
but I really don't want to
say this out loud.

705
00:51:48,742 --> 00:51:50,844
Wait, why are you smiling?

706
00:51:51,144 --> 00:51:52,179
Huh?

707
00:52:27,114 --> 00:52:29,216
Did you see off your mother well?

708
00:52:29,917 --> 00:52:31,084
Yes. Of course.

709
00:52:32,486 --> 00:52:34,821
And you gave the deceased's family
the death certificate?

710
00:52:34,888 --> 00:52:37,357
Yes. I did.

711
00:52:44,898 --> 00:52:46,133
Dr Yoon. About yesterday...

712
00:52:46,200 --> 00:52:49,503
One shouldn't talk about
what people did when they were drunk.

713
00:52:51,038 --> 00:52:53,740
That's basic drinking etiquette.

714
00:53:00,981 --> 00:53:05,052
But you know, you lost your chance at...

715
00:53:05,118 --> 00:53:07,664
...getting a 15 percent pay raise andextra
100,000 dollars for your research.

716
00:53:07,754 --> 00:53:09,356
And you turned your back on Director Do...

717
00:53:09,423 --> 00:53:11,543
...because of the incident
with the death certificate.

718
00:53:12,326 --> 00:53:15,195
So going back to the main hospital
will be difficult for the time being.

719
00:53:16,797 --> 00:53:17,731
Oh well.

720
00:53:17,798 --> 00:53:21,602
It looks like you're stuck at
this cruddy excuse for a hospital for now.

721
00:53:23,370 --> 00:53:24,638
Yes, exactly.

722
00:53:25,305 --> 00:53:28,375
I lost all those great offers and...

723
00:53:28,442 --> 00:53:30,777
...my chance at returning
to the main hospital.

724
00:53:31,979 --> 00:53:33,180
Thinking about spending this
long, long winter...

725
00:53:33,247 --> 00:53:36,950
...at this cruddy excuse
of a hospital for now...

726
00:53:37,017 --> 00:53:39,620
...makes me feel frustrated already.

727
00:53:42,222 --> 00:53:45,993
So... go out with me, Yoon Seo-Jung.

728
00:53:50,797 --> 00:53:52,432
Seriously...

729
00:53:57,371 --> 00:53:58,772
I can't?

730
00:54:01,208 --> 00:54:05,746
I can't go out with you, Dr Yoon?

731
00:54:07,948 --> 00:54:08,916
No.

732
00:54:09,516 --> 00:54:10,517
You can't.

733
00:54:16,890 --> 00:54:17,991
And what's the reason?

734
00:54:19,793 --> 00:54:22,496
I want to know why you keep avoiding me.

735
00:54:23,363 --> 00:54:24,898
Can't you tell me?

736
00:54:26,200 --> 00:54:27,968
No, I can't.

737
00:54:31,738 --> 00:54:33,640
But you like me too, Dr Yoon.

738
00:54:34,174 --> 00:54:35,943
Am I wrong?

739
00:54:38,979 --> 00:54:40,914
Am I wrong?

740
00:54:43,917 --> 00:54:45,919
Three strikes and you're out, right?

741
00:54:47,254 --> 00:54:48,856
You have one more chance left, then.

742
00:55:28,929 --> 00:55:30,030
What are you doing there?

743
00:55:31,665 --> 00:55:32,699
Huh?

744
00:55:33,467 --> 00:55:36,703
Oh, I was just heading to the ER.

745
00:55:52,586 --> 00:55:53,587
Yes, Father?

746
00:55:54,454 --> 00:55:56,123
There's something you must do for me.

747
00:55:59,126 --> 00:56:00,060
What?

748
00:56:00,794 --> 00:56:02,874
You set a date for me
to be admitted to the hospital?

749
00:56:03,130 --> 00:56:04,131
Yes.

750
00:56:04,198 --> 00:56:06,533
We've finally decided on a date.

751
00:56:06,600 --> 00:56:11,538
You can come in tomorrow afternoon
whenever it's convenient for you.

752
00:56:11,605 --> 00:56:15,375
Will we go straight into surgery
after that, then?

753
00:56:15,442 --> 00:56:20,981
We'll be checking on your body's condition
for two or three days first.

754
00:56:21,048 --> 00:56:24,518
Oh, with those fancy gadgets
that I bought you, right?

755
00:56:25,252 --> 00:56:28,455
Yes, with those fancy gadgets
that you bought us.

756
00:56:28,522 --> 00:56:34,061
If the test results come out okay,
we'll do the surgery early next week.

757
00:56:34,828 --> 00:56:36,430
It's a simple procedure,

758
00:56:37,030 --> 00:56:39,499
so you won't have to be
hospitalized for too long.

759
00:56:43,537 --> 00:56:47,140
Make sure you're one of the doctors
performing that surgery.

760
00:56:47,508 --> 00:56:49,643
But I'm a general surgeon. How can I...?

761
00:56:49,710 --> 00:56:52,513
That's for you to figure out, obviously!

762
00:56:52,579 --> 00:56:54,047
You have a brain, don't you?

763
00:56:55,649 --> 00:57:00,621
Make sure you report each and
every thing that happens in there to me.

764
00:57:01,288 --> 00:57:04,525
I must know everything.

765
00:57:21,074 --> 00:57:22,142
Oh, really?

766
00:57:22,209 --> 00:57:23,329
Yoon Seo-Jung is doing that?

767
00:57:23,644 --> 00:57:26,213
She's been reading books related
to this ever since that day.

768
00:57:26,280 --> 00:57:27,200
I'm quite proud of her.

769
00:57:28,081 --> 00:57:30,150
I thought it'd be good for you to know.

770
00:57:30,217 --> 00:57:31,485
Oh, yes.

771
00:57:31,552 --> 00:57:34,188
Have you decided on
a team for the surgery yet?

772
00:57:34,354 --> 00:57:37,357
I do have a rough idea in my mind, but...

773
00:57:43,063 --> 00:57:45,332
...I'm going to think about it for...

774
00:57:46,099 --> 00:57:48,802
...a few more days before
I finalize the roster.

775
00:57:48,869 --> 00:57:50,037
I see.

776
00:57:51,104 --> 00:57:55,309
It'd be nice for Dr Yoon to
get an opportunity this time around.

777
00:57:56,243 --> 00:57:59,580
That's just my opinion, though.

778
00:58:00,113 --> 00:58:01,915
I'll be hanging up now, Nurse Oh.

779
00:58:05,886 --> 00:58:06,854
What brings you here?

780
00:58:13,360 --> 00:58:15,829
What? What is it? Go ahead.

781
00:58:20,467 --> 00:58:24,471
Regarding Chairman Shin's
artificial heart surgery...

782
00:58:25,205 --> 00:58:27,574
You can't even call it
a full-blown surgery, really.

783
00:58:27,641 --> 00:58:29,710
We're just swapping out the batteries.

784
00:58:29,977 --> 00:58:34,081
May I be your main assistant
during that surgery?

785
00:58:39,620 --> 00:58:41,989
But you're a general surgeon.

786
00:58:42,189 --> 00:58:46,827
I observed a heart transplant surgery
once when I was an intern.

787
00:58:46,894 --> 00:58:49,663
After that, I've observed
one aortic valve surgery...

788
00:58:49,730 --> 00:58:51,832
...and four cardiovascular
bypass surgeries.

789
00:58:51,899 --> 00:58:53,367
I've also observed one ECMO surgery.

790
00:58:53,901 --> 00:58:55,936
And I've assisted in
two of the surgeries I've observed.

791
00:58:56,003 --> 00:58:58,705
But if you come in as my main assistant,

792
00:58:58,772 --> 00:59:00,908
you'll be stealing that opportunity
from Yoon Seo-Jung.

793
00:59:00,974 --> 00:59:03,110
Are you aware of that?

794
00:59:03,544 --> 00:59:07,114
Is it... not possible then?

795
00:59:15,455 --> 00:59:17,224
Aren't you looking forward to it all?

796
00:59:19,459 --> 00:59:23,463
Who will end up on
Teacher Kim's surgical team?

797
00:59:24,598 --> 00:59:25,599
Who knows?

798
00:59:26,633 --> 00:59:28,602
We may not know...

799
00:59:28,669 --> 00:59:30,971
...but those who will be
chosen sure are lucky.

800
01:00:02,921 --> 01:00:08,459
Romantic Doctor, Teacher Kim
